102
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:41,039
And then you try to close them on a call and try to swipe their credit card while you're on a sales call.

103
00:05:41,039 --> 00:05:43,440
Step four, the deposit framework.

104
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:46,080
Don't say, "Please pay for my non-existing solution."

105
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,800
Or even make them pay monthly for something that is not there.

106
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:55,840
The better way is deliver as much value as you can and give them a 100% refundable deposit offer.

107
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:58,160
Say, for example, $500 you take down.

108
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:02,000
It's a onetime payment that you take and the buyer gets full access to your product.

109
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,880
Once it launches, you can also put some urgency in there.

110
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,759
For example, this secures you a spot in the first launch of the product.

111
00:06:07,759 --> 00:06:09,759
Also, one big point, go high ticket.

112
00:06:09,759 --> 00:06:14,319
If you go this route and do a do a call with the buyer, don't charge them $20 or something.

113
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:17,199
Charge them something serious so you know they are in.

114
00:06:17,199 --> 00:06:20,800
Nothing validates your idea more than someone swiping their credit card.

115
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,639
Step five, give it some time to incubate.

116
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:27,919
